## Context-Aware Letters

| Letter | Position | Roman | Example |
|--------|----------|-------|---------|
| յ | word start | h | յոյս = huys |
| յ | middle/end | y | բայ = pay |
| ո | before consonant | vo | ոչ = voch |
| ո | after consonant | o | կո = go |
| ե | word start | ye | եղ = yegh |
| ե | middle/end | e | բեր = ber |
| ւ | in diphthong ու/իւ | oo/yoo | իւր = yur |
| ւ | between vowels | v | այւ = ayv |

| ոյ | not word-final, or 3-letter word | uy | յոյս = huys |
| ոյ | word-final (4+ letters) | o (յ silent) | — |

---

## Diphthongs

| Pair | Roman | Example |
|------|-------|---------|
| ու | oo | ուր = oor (where) |
| իւ | yoo | իւր = yur (his/her), իւղ = yoogh (oil) |
| եա | ea | retained in classical |
| էյ | ey | retained in clasical  |
| այ | ay | when at the end of a word more than three characters, the յ is silent|
| ոյ | uy | when at the end of a word more than three characters, this is "o" as in "oh"|

